  "body": "**input tag bug**\n\nI am following the official document ([here](https://facebook.github.io/react/docs/forms.html)) . In this document, when user input event occurs we should controller over input value with `state` and  `setState` method.\n\nHowever, when I tried this code below \n\n``` javascript\n_onQuery(e) {\n  this.setState({ query: e.target.value });\n}\nrender() {\n  return (<input type=\"text\" onChange={e => this._onQuery(e)} value={this.state.query} />);\n}\n```\n\nIt works very well in all browser in PC but not in mobile browser(chrome and safari). The bug is like that when I enter some inputs then I remove by a letter, the cursor get position in second line even though I remove first letter.\n\nI guessed the component rendered with `setState` method before the cursor get positioned. So I tried this code.\n\n``` javascript\n_onQuery(e) {\n  setTimeout(() => this.setState({ query: e.target.value }), 0);\n}\n```\n\nThen it works well. If my guess is right, it should be fixed.\nThank you.\n",
